Sinuston

Markdown doc
Formel fr Sinuston
$ A\sin(2\ * \pi\ * \ f \ * \ t + \phi) $
A = Amplitude
f = Frequenz
t = Zeitintervall
$\phi$ = Phase

In[66]:
A = 0.5
f = 440
sr = 44100
sineTone = np.zeros(sr)
pha = 0
t = np.linspace(0,2*np.pi,sr)
#for t in range(sr * 2):
#  sineTone[t] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * f * (float(t) / float(sr)) + pha)
sineTone = np.sin(t * f + pha)
plt.xlim(sr/f)
plt.plot(sineTone)
display(Audio(sineTone,rate=sr))

fglis = 100

for t in range(sr):
  sineGlis[t] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * fglis * ((t) / (sr)))
  fglis += inc_t
plt.xlim(sr/8)
#plt.axis([max(sineGlis), min(sineGlis), -1,1])
plt.plot(sineGlis)

#steigung/increment fr ein sample
inc_t = ((1000 - 100) / sr)
fglis = 100
lin = np.zeros(sr)
for t in range(sr):
  lin[t] = fglis
  fglis += inc_t
plt.plot(lin)

In[58]:
carrier = deepcopy(sineTone)
mod = np.zeros(sr)
f = 2
for t in range(sr):
  mod[t] = np.sin(2 * np.pi * f * (t / sr))

plt.plot(mod)
carrier *= mod
plt.plot(carrier)
display(Audio(carrier,rate=sr))

In[77]:
carrier2 = deepcopy(sineTone)
mod2 = np.zeros(sr)
f = 1
for t in range(sr):
  mod2[t] = (np.cos(2 * np.pi * f * (t / sr) + np.pi*0.5) * 0.5 ) + 0.5

plt.plot(mod2)
carrier2 *= mod2
plt.plot(carrier2)
display(Audio(carrier2,rate=sr))

FM Synthesis

FM doc
"FmFormel" $ A \ sin( \ * t \ + B \ * sin(\omega _{m} \ * \ t ) $

In[89]:
wt2 = np.zeros(sr)
carrierfreq = 220
moddepth = 880
modfreq = 440
print(moddepth/modfreq)
for i in range(sr):
    wt2[i] = 0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * (float(i) / float(sr)) * carrierfreq + moddepth/modfreq * np.sin(2 * np.pi * (float(i) / float(sr)) * modfreq))
plt.plot(wt2)
plt.ylim(-1,1)
plt.xlim(0,sr / carrierfreq )
display(Audio(wt2, rate = sr))
